International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: 13 Feb 2013
Source: OIE [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=13000


Contagious equine metritis, United States of America
---------------------------------------------------
Information received on 13 Feb 2013 from Dr John Clifford, Deputy Administrator, Animal and Plant Health Inspection Service, United States Department of Agriculture, Washington, United States of America

Summary:
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 22 Jan 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 06 Feb 2013
Report date: 12 Feb 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 13 Feb 2013
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: June 2012
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Taylorella equigenitalis
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Fresno County, Fresno, California
Date of start of the outbreak: 22 Jan 2013
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: A 17-year-old Lusitano mare has been confirmed culture positive by the USDA APHIS National Veterinary Services Laboratories (NVSL) for _Taylorella equigenitalis_, the bacterium that causes contagious equine metritis (CEM). The CEM confirmed positive mare was identified as part of a pre-breeding health examination.

Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / ** / ** / 0.00 percent / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter
**Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: A comprehensive epidemiological investigation is being conducted by the California Departments of Food and Agriculture (CDFA) and the United States Department of Agriculture (USDA) officials. Update as of 11 Feb 2013:
- Information collected to date indicates the CEM positive mare had limited breeding activities, and no horses located outside of California are currently known to have been exposed.
- The CEM positive mare has been placed under quarantine.
- The epidemiological and diagnostic investigation conducted to date finds no relationship between the positive mare and any previous U.S. cases of CEM.
- The positive mare has begun to be treated following the approved protocols for CEM.

Control measures:
Measures applied:
- Quarantine
- No vaccination
- Treatment of affected animals (all testing and treatment protocols are being done following federal, international, and expert guidance and requirements)
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Veterinary Services Laboratories (NVSL) (National laboratory) / Equidae / pathogenic agent isolation on culture / 06 Feb 2013 / Positive

Future Reporting:
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

Map of outbreak locations [go to OIE site to see map]

